#: ../../../news.rst:12 ../../../news.rst:787 ../../../news.rst:2055
#: ../../../news.rst:2183 ../../../news.rst:3274
msgid "Security bug fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:14
msgid ""
"Values from the ``Referrer-Policy`` header of HTTP responses are no longer "
"executed as Python callables. See the `cwxj-rr6w-m6w7`_ security advisory "
"for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:20
msgid ""
"In line with the `standard <https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#http-redirect-"
"fetch>`__, 301 redirects of ``POST`` requests are converted into ``GET`` "
"requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:24
msgid ""
"Converting to a ``GET`` request implies not only a method change, but also "
"omitting the body and ``Content-*`` headers in the redirect request. On "
"cross-origin redirects (for example, cross-domain redirects), this is "
"effectively a security bug fix for scenarios where the body contains secrets."
msgstr ""

