msgid "(:issue:`6540`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1582
msgid ""
"The ``response_body`` argument of :meth:`ImagesPipeline.convert_image "
"<scrapy.pipelines.images.ImagesPipeline.convert_image>` is now positional-"
"only, as it was changed from optional to required. (:issue:`6500`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1587
msgid ""
"The ``convert`` argument of :func:`scrapy.utils.conf.build_component_list` "
"is now positional-only, as the preceding argument (``custom``) was removed. "
"(:issue:`6500`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1591
msgid ""
"The ``overwrite_output`` argument of :func:`scrapy.utils.conf."
"feed_process_params_from_cli` is now positional-only, as the preceding "
"argument (``output_format``) was removed. (:issue:`6500`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1599
msgid ""
"Removed the ``scrapy.utils.request.request_fingerprint()`` function, "
"deprecated in Scrapy 2.7.0. (:issue:`6212`, :issue:`6213`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1603
msgid ""
"Removed support for value ``\"2.6\"`` of setting "
"``REQUEST_FINGERPRINTER_IMPLEMENTATION``, deprecated in Scrapy 2.7.0. (:"
"issue:`6212`, :issue:`6213`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1607
msgid ""
":class:`~scrapy.dupefilters.RFPDupeFilter` subclasses now require supporting "
"the ``fingerprinter`` parameter in their ``__init__`` method, introduced in "
"Scrapy 2.7.0. (:issue:`6102`, :issue:`6113`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1612
msgid ""
"Removed the ``scrapy.downloadermiddlewares.decompression`` module, "
"deprecated in Scrapy 2.7.0. (:issue:`6100`, :issue:`6113`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1616
msgid ""
"Removed the ``scrapy.utils.response.response_httprepr()`` function, "
"deprecated in Scrapy 2.6.0. (:issue:`6111`, :issue:`6116`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1620
msgid ""
"Spiders with spider-level HTTP authentication, i.e. with the ``http_user`` "
"or ``http_pass`` attributes, must now define ``http_auth_domain`` as well, "
"which was introduced in Scrapy 2.5.1. (:issue:`6103`, :issue:`6113`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1625
msgid ""
":ref:`Media pipelines <topics-media-pipeline>` methods ``file_path()``, "
"``file_downloaded()``, ``get_images()``, ``image_downloaded()``, "
"``media_downloaded()``, ``media_to_download()``, and ``thumb_path()`` must "
"now support an ``item`` parameter, added in Scrapy 2.4.0. (:issue:`6107`, :"
"issue:`6113`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1631
msgid ""
"The ``__init__()`` and ``from_crawler()`` methods of :ref:`feed storage "
"backend classes <topics-feed-storage>` must now support the keyword-only "
"``feed_options`` parameter, introduced in Scrapy 2.4.0. (:issue:`6105`, :"
"issue:`6113`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1636
msgid ""
"Removed the ``scrapy.loader.common`` and ``scrapy.loader.processors`` "
"modules, deprecated in Scrapy 2.3.0. (:issue:`6106`, :issue:`6113`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1640
msgid ""
"Removed the ``scrapy.utils.misc.extract_regex()`` function, deprecated in "
"Scrapy 2.3.0. (:issue:`6106`, :issue:`6113`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1644
msgid ""
"Removed the ``scrapy.http.JSONRequest`` class, replaced with ``JsonRequest`` "
"in Scrapy 1.8.0. (:issue:`6110`, :issue:`6113`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1648
msgid ""
"``scrapy.utils.log.logformatter_adapter`` no longer supports missing "
"``args``, ``level``, or ``msg`` parameters, and no longer supports a "
"``format`` parameter, all scenarios that were deprecated in Scrapy 1.0.0. (:"
"issue:`6109`, :issue:`6116`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1653
msgid ""
"A custom class assigned to the :setting:`SPIDER_LOADER_CLASS` setting that "
"does not implement the :class:`~scrapy.interfaces.ISpiderLoader` interface "
"will now raise a :exc:`zope.interface.verify.DoesNotImplement` exception at "
"run time. Non-compliant classes have been triggering a deprecation warning "
"since Scrapy 1.0.0. (:issue:`6101`, :issue:`6113`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1660
msgid ""
"Removed the ``--output-format``/``-t`` command line option, deprecated in "
"Scrapy 2.1.0. ``-O <URI>:<FORMAT>`` should be used instead. (:issue:`6500`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1664
msgid ""
"Running :meth:`~scrapy.crawler.Crawler.crawl` more than once on the same :"
"class:`~scrapy.crawler.Crawler` instance, deprecated in Scrapy 2.11.0, now "
"raises an exception. (:issue:`6500`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1669
msgid ""
"Subclassing :class:`~scrapy.downloadermiddlewares.httpcompression."
"HttpCompressionMiddleware` without support for the ``crawler`` argument in "
"``__init__()`` and without a custom ``from_crawler()`` method, deprecated in "
"Scrapy 2.5.0, is no longer allowed. (:issue:`6500`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1676
msgid ""
"Removed the ``EXCEPTIONS_TO_RETRY`` attribute of :class:`~scrapy."
"downloadermiddlewares.retry.RetryMiddleware`, deprecated in Scrapy 2.10.0. (:"
"issue:`6500`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1681
msgid ""
"Removed support for :ref:`S3 feed exports <topics-feed-storage-s3>` without "
"the boto3_ package installed, deprecated in Scrapy 2.10.0. (:issue:`6500`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1685
msgid ""
"Removed the ``scrapy.extensions.feedexport._FeedSlot`` class, deprecated in "
"Scrapy 2.10.0. (:issue:`6500`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1689
msgid ""
"Removed the ``scrapy.pipelines.images.NoimagesDrop`` exception, deprecated "
"in Scrapy 2.8.0. (:issue:`6500`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1693
msgid ""
"The ``response_body`` argument of :meth:`ImagesPipeline.convert_image "
"<scrapy.pipelines.images.ImagesPipeline.convert_image>` is now required, not "
"passing it was deprecated in Scrapy 2.8.0. (:issue:`6500`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1698
msgid ""
"Removed the ``custom`` argument of :func:`scrapy.utils.conf."
"build_component_list`, deprecated in Scrapy 2.10.0. (:issue:`6500`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1703
msgid ""
"Removed the ``scrapy.utils.reactor.get_asyncio_event_loop_policy()`` "
"function, deprecated in Scrapy 2.9.0. Use :func:`asyncio.get_event_loop` and "
"related standard library functions instead. (:issue:`6500`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1711
msgid ""
"The ``from_settings()`` methods of the :ref:`Scrapy components <topics-"
"components>` that have them are now deprecated. ``from_crawler()`` should "
"now be used instead. Affected components:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1721
msgid ":class:`scrapy.spidermiddlewares.urllength.UrlLengthMiddleware`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1725
msgid ""
"It's now deprecated to have a ``from_settings()`` method but no "
"``from_crawler()`` method in 3rd-party :ref:`Scrapy components <topics-"
"components>`. You can define a simple ``from_crawler()`` method that calls "
"``cls.from_settings(crawler.settings)`` to fix this if you don't want to "
"refactor the code. Note that if you have a ``from_crawler()`` method Scrapy "
"will not call the ``from_settings()`` method so the latter can be removed. (:"
"issue:`6540`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1734
msgid ""
"The initialization API of :class:`scrapy.pipelines.media.MediaPipeline` and "
"its subclasses was improved and some old usage scenarios are now deprecated "
"(see also the \"Backward-incompatible changes\" section). Specifically:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1738
msgid ""
"It's deprecated to define an ``__init__()`` method that doesn't take a "
"``crawler`` argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1740
msgid ""
"It's deprecated to call an ``__init__()`` method without passing a "
"``crawler`` argument. If it's passed, it's also deprecated to pass a "
"``settings`` argument, which will be ignored anyway."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1743
msgid ""
"Calling ``from_settings()`` is deprecated, use ``from_crawler()`` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1745
msgid ""
"Overriding ``from_settings()`` is deprecated, override ``from_crawler()`` "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1750
msgid ""
"The ``REQUEST_FINGERPRINTER_IMPLEMENTATION`` setting is now deprecated. (:"
"issue:`6212`, :issue:`6213`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1753
msgid ""
"The ``scrapy.utils.misc.create_instance()`` function is now deprecated, use :"
"func:`scrapy.utils.misc.build_from_crawler` instead. (:issue:`5523`, :issue:"
"`5884`, :issue:`6162`, :issue:`6169`, :issue:`6540`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1757
msgid ""
"``scrapy.core.downloader.Downloader._get_slot_key()`` is deprecated, use :"
"meth:`scrapy.core.downloader.Downloader.get_slot_key` instead. (:issue:"
"`6340`, :issue:`6352`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1761
msgid ""
"``scrapy.utils.defer.process_chain_both()`` is now deprecated. (:issue:"
"`6397`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1764
msgid ""
"``scrapy.twisted_version`` is now deprecated, you should instead use :attr:"
"`twisted.version` directly (but note that it's an ``incremental.Version`` "
"object, not a tuple). (:issue:`6509`, :issue:`6512`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1769
msgid ""
"``scrapy.utils.python.flatten()`` and ``scrapy.utils.python.iflatten()`` are "
"now deprecated. (:issue:`6517`, :issue:`6519`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1773
msgid ""
"``scrapy.utils.python.equal_attributes()`` is now deprecated. (:issue:"
"`6517`, :issue:`6519`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1776
msgid ""
"``scrapy.utils.request.request_authenticate()`` is now deprecated, you "
"should instead just set the ``Authorization`` header directly. (:issue:"
"`6517`, :issue:`6519`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1780
msgid ""
"``scrapy.utils.serialize.ScrapyJSONDecoder`` is now deprecated, it didn't "
"contain any code since Scrapy 1.0.0. (:issue:`6517`, :issue:`6519`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1784
msgid ""
"``scrapy.utils.test.assert_samelines()`` is now deprecated. (:issue:`6517`, :"
"issue:`6519`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1787
msgid ""
"``scrapy.extensions.feedexport.build_storage()`` is now deprecated. You can "
"instead call the builder callable directly. (:issue:`6540`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1794
msgid ""
"``scrapy.Spider.start_requests()`` can now yield items. (:issue:`5289`, :"
"issue:`6417`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1797
msgid ""
"Some spider middlewares may need to be updated for Scrapy 2.12 support "
"before you can use them in combination with the ability to yield items from "
"``start_requests()``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1801
msgid ""
"Added a new :class:`~scrapy.http.Response` subclass, :class:`~scrapy.http."
"JsonResponse`, for responses with a `JSON MIME type <https://mimesniff.spec."
"whatwg.org/#json-mime-type>`_. (:issue:`6069`, :issue:`6171`, :issue:`6174`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1806
msgid ""
"The :class:`~scrapy.extensions.logstats.LogStats` extension now adds "
"``items_per_minute`` and ``responses_per_minute`` to the :ref:`stats <topics-"
"stats>` when the spider closes. (:issue:`4110`, :issue:`4111`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1811
msgid ""
"Added :setting:`CLOSESPIDER_PAGECOUNT_NO_ITEM` which allows closing the "
"spider if no items were scraped in a set amount of time. (:issue:`6434`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1815
msgid ""
"User-defined cookies can now include the ``secure`` field. (:issue:`6357`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1818
msgid ""
"Added component getters to :class:`~scrapy.crawler.Crawler`: :meth:`~scrapy."
"crawler.Crawler.get_addon`, :meth:`~scrapy.crawler.Crawler."
"get_downloader_middleware`, :meth:`~scrapy.crawler.Crawler.get_extension`, :"
"meth:`~scrapy.crawler.Crawler.get_item_pipeline`, :meth:`~scrapy.crawler."
"Crawler.get_spider_middleware`. (:issue:`6181`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1826
msgid ""
"Slot delay updates by the :ref:`AutoThrottle extension <topics-"
"autothrottle>` based on response latencies can now be disabled for specific "
"requests via the :reqmeta:`autothrottle_dont_adjust_delay` meta key. (:issue:"
"`6246`, :issue:`6527`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1832
msgid ""
"If :setting:`SPIDER_LOADER_WARN_ONLY` is set to ``True``, :class:`~scrapy."
"spiderloader.SpiderLoader` does not raise :exc:`SyntaxError` but emits a "
"warning instead. (:issue:`6483`, :issue:`6484`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1837
msgid ""
"Added support for multiple-compressed responses (ones with several encodings "
