#: ../../../news.rst:2697
msgid "Scrapy 2.8.0 (2023-02-02)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2699
msgid ""
"This is a maintenance release, with minor features, bug fixes, and cleanups."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2704
msgid ""
"The ``scrapy.utils.gz.read1`` function, deprecated in Scrapy 2.0, has now "
"been removed. Use the :meth:`~io.BufferedIOBase.read1` method of :class:"
"`~gzip.GzipFile` instead. (:issue:`5719`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2709
msgid ""
"The ``scrapy.utils.python.to_native_str`` function, deprecated in Scrapy "
"2.0, has now been removed. Use :func:`scrapy.utils.python.to_unicode` "
"instead. (:issue:`5719`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2714
msgid ""
"The ``scrapy.utils.python.MutableChain.next`` method, deprecated in Scrapy "
"2.0, has now been removed. Use :meth:`~scrapy.utils.python.MutableChain."
"__next__` instead. (:issue:`5719`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2719
msgid ""
"The ``scrapy.linkextractors.FilteringLinkExtractor`` class, deprecated in "
"Scrapy 2.0, has now been removed. Use :class:`LinkExtractor <scrapy."
"linkextractors.lxmlhtml.LxmlLinkExtractor>` instead. (:issue:`5720`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2725
msgid ""
"Support for using environment variables prefixed with ``SCRAPY_`` to "
"override settings, deprecated in Scrapy 2.0, has now been removed. (:issue:"
"`5724`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2729
msgid ""
"Support for the ``noconnect`` query string argument in proxy URLs, "
"deprecated in Scrapy 2.0, has now been removed. We expect proxies that used "
"to need it to work fine without it. (:issue:`5731`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2734
msgid ""
"The ``scrapy.utils.python.retry_on_eintr`` function, deprecated in Scrapy "
"2.3, has now been removed. (:issue:`5719`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2738
msgid ""
"The ``scrapy.utils.python.WeakKeyCache`` class, deprecated in Scrapy 2.4, "
"has now been removed. (:issue:`5719`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2742
msgid ""
"The ``scrapy.utils.boto.is_botocore()`` function, deprecated in Scrapy 2.4, "
"has now been removed. (:issue:`5719`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2750
msgid ""
":exc:`scrapy.pipelines.images.NoimagesDrop` is now deprecated. (:issue:"
"`5368`, :issue:`5489`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2753
msgid ""
":meth:`ImagesPipeline.convert_image <scrapy.pipelines.images.ImagesPipeline."
"convert_image>` must now accept a ``response_body`` parameter. (:issue:"
"`3055`, :issue:`3689`, :issue:`4753`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2762
msgid ""
"Applied black_ coding style to files generated with the :command:`genspider` "
"and :command:`startproject` commands. (:issue:`5809`, :issue:`5814`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2768
msgid ""
":setting:`FEED_EXPORT_ENCODING` is now set to ``\"utf-8\"`` in the "
"``settings.py`` file that the :command:`startproject` command generates. "
"With this value, JSON exports won’t force the use of escape sequences for "
"non-ASCII characters. (:issue:`5797`, :issue:`5800`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2774
msgid ""
"The :class:`~scrapy.extensions.memusage.MemoryUsage` extension now logs the "
"peak memory usage during checks, and the binary unit MiB is now used to "
"avoid confusion. (:issue:`5717`, :issue:`5722`, :issue:`5727`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2779
msgid ""
"The ``callback`` parameter of :class:`~scrapy.Request` can now be set to :"
"func:`scrapy.http.request.NO_CALLBACK`, to distinguish it from ``None``, as "
"the latter indicates that the default spider callback (:meth:`~scrapy.Spider."
"parse`) is to be used. (:issue:`5798`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2789
msgid ""
"Enabled unsafe legacy SSL renegotiation to fix access to some outdated "
"websites. (:issue:`5491`, :issue:`5790`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2793
msgid ""
"Fixed STARTTLS-based email delivery not working with Twisted 21.2.0 and "
"better. (:issue:`5386`, :issue:`5406`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2797
msgid ""
"Fixed the :meth:`finish_exporting` method of :ref:`item exporters <topics-"
"exporters>` not being called for empty files. (:issue:`5537`, :issue:`5758`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2801
msgid ""
"Fixed HTTP/2 responses getting only the last value for a header when "
"multiple headers with the same name are received. (:issue:`5777`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2805
msgid ""
"Fixed an exception raised by the :command:`shell` command on some cases "
"when :ref:`using asyncio <using-asyncio>`. (:issue:`5740`, :issue:`5742`, :"
"issue:`5748`, :issue:`5759`, :issue:`5760`, :issue:`5771`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2810
msgid ""
"When using :class:`~scrapy.spiders.CrawlSpider`, callback keyword arguments "
"(``cb_kwargs``) added to a request in the ``process_request`` callback of a :"
"class:`~scrapy.spiders.Rule` will no longer be ignored. (:issue:`5699`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2815
msgid ""
"The :ref:`images pipeline <images-pipeline>` no longer re-encodes JPEG "
"files. (:issue:`3055`, :issue:`3689`, :issue:`4753`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2819
msgid ""
"Fixed the handling of transparent WebP images by the :ref:`images pipeline "
"<images-pipeline>`. (:issue:`3072`, :issue:`5766`, :issue:`5767`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2823
msgid ""
":func:`scrapy.shell.inspect_response` no longer inhibits ``SIGINT`` "
"(Ctrl+C). (:issue:`2918`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2827
msgid ""
":class:`LinkExtractor <scrapy.linkextractors.lxmlhtml.LxmlLinkExtractor>` "
"with ``unique=False`` no longer filters out links that have identical URL "
"*and* text. (:issue:`3798`, :issue:`3799`, :issue:`4695`, :issue:`5458`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2832
msgid ""
":class:`~scrapy.downloadermiddlewares.robotstxt.RobotsTxtMiddleware` now "
"ignores URL protocols that do not support ``robots.txt`` (``data://``, "
"``file://``). (:issue:`5807`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2837
msgid ""
"Silenced the ``filelock`` debug log messages introduced in Scrapy 2.6. (:"
"issue:`5753`, :issue:`5754`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2840
msgid ""
"Fixed the output of ``scrapy -h`` showing an unintended ``**commands**`` "
"line. (:issue:`5709`, :issue:`5711`, :issue:`5712`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2844
msgid ""
"Made the active project indication in the output of :ref:`commands <topics-"
"commands>` more clear. (:issue:`5715`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2852
msgid ""
"Documented how to :ref:`debug spiders from Visual Studio Code <debug-"
"vscode>`. (:issue:`5721`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2856
msgid ""
"Documented how :setting:`DOWNLOAD_DELAY` affects per-domain concurrency. (:"
"issue:`5083`, :issue:`5540`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2859
msgid "Improved consistency. (:issue:`5761`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2862
msgid "Fixed typos. (:issue:`5714`, :issue:`5744`, :issue:`5764`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:2869
msgid ""
"Applied :ref:`black coding style <coding-style>`, sorted import statements, "
