#: ../../../news.rst:4736
msgid ":class:`scrapy.core.downloader.handlers.datauri.DataURIDownloadHandler`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:4738
msgid ":class:`scrapy.core.downloader.handlers.file.FileDownloadHandler`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:4740
msgid ""
"Use the ``from_settings`` or ``from_crawler`` class methods to expose such a "
"parameter to your custom download handlers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:4743
msgid "(:issue:`4126`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:4745
msgid ""
"We have refactored the :class:`scrapy.core.scheduler.Scheduler` class and "
"related queue classes (see :setting:`SCHEDULER_PRIORITY_QUEUE`, :setting:"
"`SCHEDULER_DISK_QUEUE` and :setting:`SCHEDULER_MEMORY_QUEUE`) to make it "
"easier to implement custom scheduler queue classes. See :ref:`2-0-0-"
"scheduler-queue-changes` below for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:4751
msgid ""
"Overridden settings are now logged in a different format. This is more in "
"line with similar information logged at startup (:issue:`4199`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:4760
msgid ""
"The :ref:`Scrapy shell <topics-shell>` no longer provides a `sel` proxy "
"object, use :meth:`response.selector <scrapy.http.TextResponse.selector>` "
"instead (:issue:`4347`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:4764
msgid "LevelDB support has been removed (:issue:`4112`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:4766
msgid ""
"The following functions have been removed from :mod:`scrapy.utils.python`: "
"``isbinarytext``, ``is_writable``, ``setattr_default``, ``stringify_dict`` (:"
"issue:`4362`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:4774
msgid ""
"Using environment variables prefixed with ``SCRAPY_`` to override settings "
"is deprecated (:issue:`4300`, :issue:`4374`, :issue:`4375`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:4777
msgid ""
":class:`scrapy.linkextractors.FilteringLinkExtractor` is deprecated, use :"
